-- India's Ratnakar Bank raises $55 mln from foreign investors
-- By Indulal PM
-- Thu Apr 10, 2014 04:40AM EDT
-- None



MUMBAI, April 10 (Reuters) - India's Ratnakar Bank Ltd raised 3.28 billion rupees ($54.6 million) from a group of investors including UK's CDC Group Plc and Asia Capital and Advisors by selling an undisclosed minority stake, the regional lender said on Thursday.

Existing investors, including International Finance Corporation, an arm of the World Bank, and Indian private equity fund Gaja Capital also made fresh investments, the bank said, without disclosing how big the stake was.